Append additional userspace packages to the Luckfox buildroot defconfig.

These packages are pulled in for the lite agent's runtime: hostapd and
dnsmasq drive the Wi-Fi soft-AP fallback when no station association
holds for 30 s; minisign verifies signed agent + image artifacts during
in-band updates; libcurl is the HTTP client the agent uses for its
heartbeat and signed-asset fetches; dropbear gives the operator a
recoverable SSH path on bench rigs without pulling in a full OpenSSH
stack; chrony keeps the system clock close enough to wall time for TLS
handshakes against the cloud relay to succeed on first boot.

Out-of-tree kernel modules (RTL8812EU Wi-Fi adapter, AIC8800DC on-board
Wi-Fi 6) are NOT enabled here — they are cross-built by the per-driver
recipes under boards/luckfox-pico-zero/drivers/ and dropped into the
rootfs as pre-built .ko files in post_overlay.

--- a/sysdrv/tools/board/buildroot/luckfox_pico_defconfig
+++ b/sysdrv/tools/board/buildroot/luckfox_pico_defconfig
@@ -74,3 +74,10 @@
 BR2_PACKAGE_UTIL_LINUX_LIBMOUNT=y
 BR2_PACKAGE_NANO=y
 BR2_PACKAGE_HOST_DTC=y
+BR2_PACKAGE_HOSTAPD=y
+BR2_PACKAGE_DNSMASQ=y
+BR2_PACKAGE_MINISIGN=y
+BR2_PACKAGE_LIBCURL=y
+BR2_PACKAGE_LIBCURL_CURL=y
+BR2_PACKAGE_DROPBEAR=y
+BR2_PACKAGE_CHRONY=y
